    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hello there,&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Let me add a couple of things here.&amp;nbsp; To the original question, if I understand it correctly, no one can switch between servers without logging all the way out to server select.&amp;nbsp; So GMs, who can help on any server, still have to log out and back in.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Guides are wonderful people who volunteer their time, but they cannot check reports.&amp;nbsp; Only employees can actually check reports.&amp;nbsp; Often guides will contact a GM to look up a report and pass along the information.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;GM Admin is an in-game rank for which commands they can access.&amp;nbsp; It is not a relative rank in the CS department.&amp;nbsp; Lead GMs are the supervisors for GMs, while most GMs are GM-Admin in game.&amp;nbsp; The rank displayed in-game does not necessarily denote your position in the organization.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Devs are often about, along with QA folks, although you will most likely not see them show up on /who all GM.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Remember to be kind to the GMs and Guides you run into.&amp;nbsp; They are trying their hardest to help you and will get to you as soon as they are able.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Brenlo the Long Time CS Guy&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Brenlo on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;03-06-2004&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;09:47 AM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
