    <item>
      <title>Re: Guides and GM's</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=13413#M13413</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Guides are generally assigned to work on a particular server.&amp;nbsp; I'm sure there are very experienced guides that 'may' have a guide account on more than one server, but this is far from the norm.&amp;nbsp; Guides are not allowed to have playable characters on the server which they regulate.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;GM's, however, do have the ability to switch servers as the need arises.&amp;nbsp; GM's usally 'check in' with guides to see if any of their special abilities are required (GM's can render services that guides cannot - like item replacement, for example), evalute the situation and move on.&amp;nbsp; While a GM can spend several hours on one server, their presence is often needed in more than one place at more than one time.&amp;nbsp; Hope this answers your question.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
