    <item>
      <title>Re: Guides and GM's</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=13490#M13490</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Apprentice guides, regular guides, and senior guides are all regulated to one paticular server. S.W.A.T. (Server Wide Assistance Team) Guides and the GMs can and do move amongst the servers as needed. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Some info most people don't know about guides.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Apprentice Guides: &lt;/STRONG&gt;These are the people recently taken into the guide program. They are the level 20 guides you see around. The only thing they can do is filter petitions, answer the few questions that may come in that guides are allowed to answer, and learn about the guide program. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Guides: &lt;/STRONG&gt;These are the people who have completed an apprentice ship. Most show up in the 50's level range. They help to filter the petitions. They can also summon players who are stuck in the geomtry of the zone, rez players who have died to a bug, settle camp disputes, summon corpses that are stuck in a place a player can't reach, and summon players to an ocean zone if, and only if ,&amp;nbsp; the boats aren't working and the gnomes aren't in game. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Senior Guides: &lt;/STRONG&gt;These are the people who have chosen to do more than normal guides. Along with the things guides have done, they can change surnames, boot players who need booting, check /reports, and occasionally run GM events.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;S.W.A.T. Guides: &lt;/STRONG&gt;Same as a regular guide, but they can move about the different servers.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;GM: &lt;/STRONG&gt;The actual Customer Service Represenatives of SoE. They are NOT devs. They have no control over what gets nerfed, changed, etc. They are the ones to handle major disputes and abuse charges. They occasionally run GM events. They do item reimbursals. They restore deleted characters. I repeat, because people don't get it sometimes. &lt;STRONG&gt;GMS ARE NOT DEVS. THEY DO NOT CONTROL WHAT IS CHANGED OR NERFED!&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;GM-Admins: &lt;/STRONG&gt;The people in charge of the GMs. They do the same as GMs, and are usually the highest GM you'll see ingame. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Devs: &lt;/STRONG&gt;The people who make the changes, fix the bugs, add things, make the nerfs, etc. It's very rare to see these people on the live servers. You'll occasionally see them on the test server, but don't count on it. &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sat, 06 Mar 2004 16:59:58 GMT</pubDate>
